msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:287
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:290
msgid "This adds more sections to `Cargo.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:291
msgid ""
"This complicates the execution path for cargo, in that it now needs to know "
"about testing frameworks."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:293
msgid ""
"Flags and command-line parameters for test and bench will now vary between "
"testing frameworks, which may confuse users as they move between crates."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:297
msgid "Rationale and alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:300
msgid ""
"We could stabilize `#[bench]` and extend libtest with setup/teardown and "
"other requested features. This would complicate the in-tree libtest, "
"introduce a barrier for community contributions, and discourage other forms "
"of testing or benchmarking."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:305
msgid "Unresolved questions"
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:308
msgid ""
"These are mostly intended to be resolved during the experimental feature. "
"Many of these have strawman proposals -- unlike the rest of this RFC, these "
"proposals have not been discussed as thoroughly. If folks feel like there's "
"consensus on some of these we can move them into the main RFC."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:313
msgid "Integration with doctests"
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:315
msgid ""
"Documentation tests are somewhat special, in that they cannot easily be "
"expressed as `TokenStream` manipulations. In the first instance, the right "
"thing to do is probably to have an implicitly defined framework called "
"`doctest` which is included in the testing set `test` by default (as "
"proposed above)."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:321
msgid ""
"Another argument for punting on doctests is that they are intended to "
"demonstrate code that the user of a library would write. They're there to "
"document _how_ something should be used, and it then makes somewhat less "
"sense to have different \"ways\" of running them."
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:333
msgid "Namespacing"
msgstr ""

#: src/2318-custom-test-frameworks.md:335
msgid ""
"Currently, two frameworks can both declare interest in the same attributes. "
"How do we deal with collisions (e.g., most test crates will want the "
"attribute `#[test]`). Do we namespace the attributes by the framework name "
"(e.g., `#[mytest::test]`)? Do we require them to be behind `#[cfg(mytest)]`?"
msgstr ""

